text: Ojeccasa (possibly from Quechua uqi lead, q'asa mountain pass, "lead pass")Resumen - Ministerio de Energía y Minas, CEDEMIN S.A.C., Actualización del Plan de Cierre de Minas de la UEA Chaquelle, see Ojeccasa is a mountain in the Chila mountain in the Andes of Peru. It is located in the Arequipa Region, Castilla Province, Choco District. Ojeccasa lies southeast of Quiscapampa.escale.minedu.gob.pe - UGEL map of the Caylloma Province 1 (Arequipa Region) showing Ojaccasa == References == Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Arequipa Region
